==English==
===Etymology===
From Latinized {{Gr.}} [[hilaris]], "cheerful", from [[Ancient Greek]] 
'''[[hιλαρός]]''' (''hilaros''), "cheerful, merry", from '''[[hίλαος]]''' (''hilaos'') "propitious, gracious, kind", from '''[[hίλημι]]''' (''hilemi'') "to be  propitious, to be gracious".

